The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, February 19, 2003 				 Mahindra unit, UK firm in pact 
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, Feb. 18: Mahindra Defence Systems, an independent division of Mahindra and Mahindra Ltd (M amp;M), has tied up with Lockheed Martin Information Systems of UK to jointly develop simulators for the Indian defence sector.																								The synergy in areas of simulation and VR-based training system is expected to offer state-of-the-art simulators to the armed forces, particularly the army, senior officials said. M amp;M had set up this division in mid-2000 to develop products for the armed forces, para-military and police. 
